      "rationale": "The assessment team determined that this factor does not apply to the present COU because the validation activity and the COU both use purely computational inputs derived from the same geometric CAD model and the same fluid property database, making parameter equivalency self-evident. No formal equivalency analysis was therefore conducted. This reasoning conflates inapplicability with absence of assessment; the correct encoding would be factorStatus 'not-applicable' with documented justification, but the factor was instead left not-assessed, creating an unacknowledged epistemic gap at Model Risk Level 3."
